---
/**
 * /case-studies/ghana-market-entry/interactive
 *
 * Browser-native cartography (per Internal Marketing Deck §07).
 *
 * Nine-section interactive replica of the Power In Numbers Ghana engine
 * deliverables. The visitor scrolls or sidebar-jumps through:
 *
 *   00  Overview           — what this artifact is, how to read it
 *   01  Question Framing   — the four anchors of the case
 *   02  Throughline        — Janelle Thompson 2011 → 2026
 *   03  AI Mirror          — individual evaluating market entry (full report iframe)
 *   04  Sovereign Mirror — Domestic Resource Mobilisation (interactive iframe)
 *   05  Sovereign Mirror — Health Financing (interactive iframe)
 *   06  Sovereign Mirror — Ghana Stabilisation Fund (interactive iframe)
 *   07  Sovereign Mirror — Annual Budget Funding Amount (interactive iframe)
 *   08  Decision-Maker Briefing — what an audit-defensible recommendation looks like
 *
 * The page is intentionally heavy on inline interactives. Iframes are sized
 * generously so the embedded sidebars and tab interactions inside each
 * Sovereign Mirror briefing remain usable. The wrapping cartography frames
 * the deliverables as primary-source artifacts of a method, not a portfolio.
 */
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
